    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; 7 Engine Service Manual - Flywheel and Flywheel Housing -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s12.4">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s12.4.1" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="7">
            <title>Crankcase Rear Cover and Power Steering Idler Shaft</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields when doing the
                        following procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If removed, install power steering idler shaft into crankcase rear cover. Make sure bore
                    of crankcase rear cover is clean.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450012022" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06117.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>External retaining ring on power steering idler shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place external retaining ring on end of power steering idler shaft without threaded
                    hole.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450012023" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Power steering idler shaft and external retaining ring in power steering idler shaft
                    installation tool ZTSE4719
                </caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Put threaded hole end of power steering idler shaft into
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_268.xml" xrefid="s12.t3">power steering idler shaft installation tool
                        ZTSE4719
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s12.t3"/>
                    to set correct
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_266.xml" xrefid="s12.t1">installed height</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s12.t1"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450012024" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Power steering idler shaft installation</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, wear safety glasses with side shields when doing the
                        following procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not allow external retaining ring to contact crankcase rear
                        cover. Contact can distort external retaining ring, affecting its function as a gear thrust
                        surface.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align power steering idler shaft in crankcase rear cover at correct location. Using
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_268.xml" xrefid="s12.t3">power steering idler shaft installation tool
                        ZTSE4719
                    </hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s12.t3"/>, drive power steering idler shaft into bore in transmission side of crankcase
                    rear cover, until power steering idler shaft installation tool bottoms out.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450012025" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd16/D1618.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Power steering idler shaft installation height</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">External retaining ring</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Power steering idler shaft</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Crankcase rear cover</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If installation tool is not available, use brass drift to install power steering idler
                    shaft in crankcase rear cover to correct height.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450012026" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D06121.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Power steering idler shaft height measurement</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure power steering idler shaft height, using a
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_268.xml" xrefid="s12.t3">dial caliper</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s12.t3"/>. Power steering idler shaft height should match
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_266.xml" xrefid="s12.t1">specification</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s12.t1"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new rear gear cover gasket.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450012027" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM10/M10120.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Application of sealant</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent personal injury or death, get help when removing or installing the crankcase rear
                        cover.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, do not allow Liquid Gasket (RTV) to set longer than 5 minutes before
                        tightening joint.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_268.xml" xrefid="s12.t3">Liquid Gasket (RTV)</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s12.t3"/>
                    at ends where crankcase and lower crankcase meet.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install crankcase rear cover with aid of an assistant.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f3450012028" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figM10/M10119.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="192px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Crankcase rear cover mounting bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M8 x 55 bolt (5)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 70 bolt (2)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">M10 x 60 bolt (4)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install 11 crankcase rear cover bolts. Tighten all bolts to
                    <hotlnk document="eges3451_267.xml" xrefid="s12.t2">special torque</hotlnk>
                    <xref refid="s12.t2"/>.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
